.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-20::.
4 different games are played: scrabble, whist, monopoly, mah-jongg
City: edinburgh, venice, rome, hamburg
1. the person traveling to venice is not the person playing scrabble##6
2. the person traveling to rome is on the right of the person traveling to hamburg##1
3. the person playing mah-jongg is not to the left of the person traveling to hamburg##8
4. the person playing monopoly is the person traveling to edinburgh##1
5. the person playing mah-jongg is somewhere between the person traveling to venice and the person traveling to edinburgh##7
6. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
7. the person traveling to rome is between the person traveling to hamburg and the person playing monopoly##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |    2     |     3      |    4    |
| Game         | whist    | mah-jongg | scrabble | monopoly |
| City   | venice | hamburg      | rome     | edinburgh     |

 